obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (38532)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38532&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Definitions.-- In this Act, and in all Central Acts and Regulations made after the commencement`
  line `of this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,`
  line
  line `(1) "abet", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, shall have the same meaning`
  line `as in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(2) "act", used with reference to an offence or a civil wrong, shall include a series of acts, and`
  line `words which refer to acts done extend also to illegal omissions;`
  line
  line `(3) "affidavit" shall include affirmation and declaration in the case of persons by law allowed to`
  line `affirm or declare instead of swearing;`
  line
  line `(4) "barrister" shall mean a barrister of England or Ireland, or a member of the Faculty of`
  line `Advocates in Scotland;`
  line
  line `(5) "British India" shall mean, as respects the period before the commencement of Part III of the`
  line `Government of India Act, 1935, all territories and places within His Majesty's dominions which were`
  line `for the time being governed by His Majesty through the Governor General of India or through any`
  line `Governor or Officer subordinate to the Governor General of India, and as respects any period after`
  line `that date and before the date of the establishment of the Dominion of India means all territories for`
  line `the time being comprised within the 'Governors Provinces and the Chief Commissioners' Provinces,`
  line `except that a reference to British India in an Indian law passed or made before the commencement of`
  line `Part III of the Government of India Act, 1935, shall not include a reference to Berar;`
  line
  line `(6) "British possession" shall mean any part of Her Majesty's dominions exclusive of the United`
  line `Kingdom, and where parts of those dominions are under both a Central and a Local Legislature, all`
  line `parts under the Central Legislature shall, for the purposes of this definition, be deemed to be one`
  line `British possession;`
  line
  line `(7) "Central Act" shall means an Act of Parliament, and shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) an Act of the Dominion Legislature or of the Indian Legislature passed before the`
  line `commencement of the Constitution, and`
  line
  line `(b) an Act made before such commencement by the Governor General in Council or the`
  line `Governor General, acting in a legislative capacity;`
  line
  line `(8) "Central Government" shall--,`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to anything done before the commencement of the Constitution, mean the`
  line `Governor General or the Governor General in Council, as the case may be; and shall include,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to functions entrusted under sub-section (1) of section 124 of the`
  line `Government of India Act, 1935, to the Government of a Province, the Provincial Government`
  line `acting within the scope of the authority given to it under that subsection; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to the administration of a Chief Commissioner's Province, the Chief`
  line `Commissioner acting within the scope of the authority given to him under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 94 of the said Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to anything done or to be done after the commencement of the Constitution,`
  line `mean the President; and shall include,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to functions entrusted under clause (1) of article 258 of the Constitution, to`
  line `the Government of a State, the State Government acting within the scope of the authority`
  line `given to it under that clause; ^2***`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to the administration of a Part C State ^3[before the commencement of the`
  line `Constitution (Seventh Amendment) Act, 1956], the Chief Commissioner or the Lieutenant Governor or the Government of a neighbouring State or other authority acting within the`
  line `scope of the authority given to him or it under article 239 or article 243 of the Constitution, as`
  line `the case may be; ^3[and`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to the administration of a Union territory, the administrator thereof acting`
  line `within the scope of the authority given to him under article 239 of the Constitution;]`
  line
  line `(9) "Chapter" shall mean a Chapter of the Act or Regulation in which the word occurs;`
  line
  line `(10) "Chief Controlling Revenue Authority" or "Chief Revenue Authority" shall mean--`
  line
  line `(a) in a State where there is a Board of Revenue, that Board;`
  line
  line `(b) in a State where there is a Revenue Commissioner, that Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(c) in Punjab, the Financial Commissioner; and`
  line
  line `(d) elsewhere, such authority as, in relation to matters enumerated in List I in the Seventh`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, the Central Government, and in relation to other matters, the State`
  line `Government, may by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint;`
  line
  line `(11) "Collector" shall mean, in a Presidency-town, the Collector of Calcutta, Madras or Bombay,`
  line `as the case may be, and elsewhere the chief officer-in-charge of the revenue-administration of a`
  line district;
  line
  line `(12) "Colony"--`
  line
  line `(a) in any Central Act passed after the commencement of Part III of the Government of India`
  line `Act, 1935, shall mean any part of His Majesty's dominions exclusive of the British Islands, the Dominions of India and Pakistan (and before the establishment of those Dominions, British`
  line `India), any Dominions as defined in the Statute of Westminister, 1931, any Province or State`
  line `forming part of any of the said Dominions, and British Burma; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any Central Act passed before the commencement of Part III of the said Act, mean any`
  line `part of His Majesty's dominions exclusive of the British Islands and of British India;`
  line
  line `and in either case where parts of those dominions are under both a Central and Local Legislature, all`
  line `parts under the Central Legislature shall, for the purposes of this definition, be deemed to be one`
  line colony.
  line
  line `(13) "Commencement" used with reference to an Act or Regulation, shall mean the day on which`
  line `the Act or Regulation comes into force;`
  line
  line `(14) "Commissioner" shall mean the chief officer-in-charge of the revenue administration of a`
  line division;
  line
  line `(15) "Constitution" shall mean the Constitution of India;`
  line
  line `(16) "Consular officer" shall include consul-general, consul, vice-consul, consular agent, proconsul and any person for the time being authorised to perform the duties of consul-general, consul,`
  line `vice-consul or consular agent;`
  line
  line `(17) "District Judge" shall mean the Judge of a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction, but`
  line `shall not include a High Court in the exercise of its ordinary or extraordinary original civil`
  line jurisdiction;
  line
  line `(18) "document" shall include any matter written, expressed or described upon any substance by`
  line `means of letters, figures or marks, or by more than one of those means which is intended to be used,`
  line `or which may be used, for the purpose of recording that matter;`
  line
  line `(19) "enactment" shall include a Regulation (as hereinafter defined) and any Regulation of the`
  line `Bengal, Madras or Bombay Code, and shall also include any provision contained in any Act or in any`
  line `such Regulation as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(20) "father", in the case of any one whose personal law permits adoption, shall include an`
  line `adoptive father;`
  line
  line `(21) "financial" year shall mean the year commencing on the first day of April;`
  line
  line `(22) a thing shall be deemed to be done in "good faith" where it is in fact done honestly, whether`
  line `it is done negligently or not;`
  line
  line `(23) "Government" or "the Government" shall include both the Central Government and any`
  line `State Government;`
  line
  line `(24) "Government securities" shall mean securities of the Central Government or of any State`
  line `Government, but in any Act or Regulation made before the commencement of the Constitution shall`
  line `not include securities of the Government of any Part B State;`
  line
  line `(25) "High Court", used with reference to civil proceedings, shall mean the highest Civil Court of`
  line `appeal (not including the Supreme Court) in the part of India in which the Act or Regulation`
  line `containing the expression operates;`
  line
  line `(26) "immovable property" shall include land, benefits to arise out of land, and things attached to`
  line `the earth, or permanently fastened to anything attached to the earth;`
  line
  line `(27) "imprisonment" shall mean imprisonment of either description as defined in the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(28) "India" shall mean,--`
  line
  line `(a) as respects any period before the establishment of the Dominion of India, British India`
  line `together with all territories of Indian Rulers then under the suzerainty of His Majesty, all`
  line `territories under the suzerainty of such an Indian Ruler, and the tribal areas;`
  line
  line `(b) as respects any period after the establishment of the Dominion of India and before the`
  line `commencement of the Constitution, all territories for the time being included in that Dominion;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) as respects any period after the commencement of the Constitution , all territories for the`
  line `time being comprised in the territory of India;`
  line
  line `(29) "Indian law" shall mean any Act, Ordinance, Regulation, rule, order, bye-law or other`
  line `instrument which before the commencement of the Constitution, had the force of law in any Province`
  line `of India or part thereof, or thereafter has the force of law in any Part A State or Part C State or Part`
  line `thereof, but does not include any Act of Parliament of the United Kingdom or any Order in Council,`
  line `rule or other instrument made under such Act;`
  line
  line `(30) "Indian State" shall mean any territory which the Central Government recognised as such a`
  line `State before the commencement of the Constitution, whether described as a State, an Estate, a Jagir`
  line `or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(31) "local authority" shall mean a municipal committee, district board, body of port`
  line `Commissioners or other authority legally entitled to, or entrusted by the Government with, the control`
  line `or management of a municipal or local fund;`
  line
  line `(32) "Magistrate" shall include every person exercising all or any of the powers of a Magistrate`
  line `under the Code of Criminal Procedure for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(33) "master", used with reference to a ship, shall mean, any person (except a pilot or harbourmaster) having for the time being control or charge of the ship;`
  line
  line `(34) "merged territories" shall mean the territories which by virtue of an order made under section`
  line `290A of the Government of India Act, 1935, were immediately before the commencement of the`
  line `Constitution being administered as if they formed part of a Governor's Province or as if they were a`
  line `Chief Commissioner's Province;`
  line
  line `(35) "month" shall mean a month reckoned according to the British calendar;`
  line
  line `(36) "movable property" shall mean property of every description, except immovable property;`
  line
  line `(37) "oath" shall include affirmation and declaration in the case of persons by law allowed to`
  line `affirm or declare instead of swearing;`
  line
  line `(38) "offence" shall mean any act or omission made punishable by any law for the time being in`
  line force;
  line
  line `(39) "official Gazette" or "Gazette" shall mean the Gazette of India or the Official Gazette of a`
  line State;
  line
  line `(40) "Part" shall mean a part of the Act or Regulation in which the word occurs;`
  line
  line `(41) "Part A State" shall mean a State for the time being specified in Part A of the First Schedule`
  line `to the Constitution, ^4[as in force before the Constitution (Seventh Amendment) Act, 1956], "Part B`
  line `State" shall mean a State for the time being specified in Part B of that Schedule and "Part C" State`
  line `shall mean a State for the time being specified in Part C of that Schedule or a territory for the time`
  line `being administered by the President under the provisions of article 243 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(42) "person" shall include any company or association or body of individuals, whether`
  line `incorporated or not;`
  line
  line `(43) "Political Agent" shall mean,--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to any territory outside India, the Principal Officer, by whatever name called,`
  line `representing the Central Government in such territory; and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to any territory within India to which the Act or Regulation containing the`
  line `expression does not extend, any officer appointed by the Central Government to exercise all or`
  line `any of the powers of a Political Agent under that Act or Regulation;`
  line
  line `(44) "Presidency-town" shall mean the local limits for the time being of the ordinary original civil`
  line `jurisdiction of the High Court of Judicature at Calcutta, Madras or Bombay, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(45) "Province" shall mean a Presidency, a Governor's Province, a Lieutenant Governors`
  line `Province or a Chief Commissioner's Province;`
  line
  line `(46) "Provincial Act" shall mean an Act made by the Governor in Council, Lieutenant Governor`
  line `in Council or Chief Commissioner in Council of a Province under any of the Indian Councils Acts or`
  line `the Government of India Act, 1915, or an Act made by the Local Legislature or the Governor of a`
  line `Province under the Government of India Act, or an Act made by the Provincial Legislature or`
  line `Governor of a Province or the Coorg Legislative Council under the Government of India Act, 1935;`
  line
  line `(47) "Provincial Government" shall mean, as respects anything done before the commencement`
  line `of the Constitution, the authority or person authorised at the relevant date to administer executive`
  line `Government in the Province in question;`
  line
  line `(48) "public nuisance" shall mean a public nuisance as defined in the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860);`
  line
  line `(49)" registered", used with reference to a document, shall mean registered in ^5`
  line `[India] under the`
  line `law for the time being in force for the registration of documents;`
  line
  line `(50) "Regulation" shall mean a Regulation made by the President ^6[under article 240 of the`
  line `Constitution and shall include a Regulation made by the President under article 243 ]thereof and a`
  line `Regulation made by the Central Government under the Government of India Act, 1870, or the`
  line `Government of India Act, 1915, or the Government of India Act, 1935;`
  line
  line `(51) "rule" shall mean a rule made in exercise of a power conferred by any enactment, and shall`
  line `include a Regulation made as a rule under any enactment;`
  line
  line `(52) "schedule" shall mean a schedule to the Act or Regulation in which the word occurs;`
  line
  line `(53) "Scheduled District" shall mean a "Scheduled District" as defined in the Scheduled Districts`
  line `Act, 1874;`
  line
  line `(54) "section" shall mean a section of the Act or Regulation in which the word occurs;`
  line
  line `(55) "ship" shall include every description of vessel used in navigation not exclusively propelled`
  line `by oars;`
  line
  line `(56) "sign", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, shall, with reference to a`
  line `person who is unable to write his name, include 'mark", with its grammatical variations and cognate`
  line expressions;
  line
  line `(57) "son", in the case of any one whose personal law permits adoption, shall include an adopted`
  line son;
  line
  line `^7[(58) "State"--`
  line
  line `(a) as respects any period before the commencement of the Constitution (Seventh`
  line `Amendment) Act, 1956, shall mean a Part A State, a Part B State or a Part C State; and`
  line
  line `(b) as respects any period after such commencement, shall mean a State specified in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution and shall include a Union territory;]`
  line
  line `(59) "State Act" shall mean an Act passed by the Legislature of a State established or continued`
  line `by the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(60) "State Government",`
  line
  line `(a) as respects anything done before the commencement of the Constitution, shall mean, in a`
  line `Part A State, the Provincial Government of the corresponding Province, in a Part B State, the authority or person authorised at the relevant date to exercise executive government in the`
  line `corresponding Acceding State, and in a Part C State, the Central Government; ^8***`
  line
  line `(b) as respects anything done ^9[after the commencement of the Constitution and before the`
  line `commencement of the Constitution (Seventh Amendment) Act, 1956], shall mean, in a Part A`
  line `State, the Governor, in a Part B State, the Rajpramukh, and in a Part C State, the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `^10[(c) as respects anything done or to be done after the commencement of the Constitution`
  line `(Seventh Amendment) Act, 1956, shall mean, in a State, the Governor, and in a Union territory, the Central Government;`
  line
  line `and shall, in relation to functions entrusted under article 258A of the Constitution to the Government`
  line `of India, include the Central Government acting within the scope of the authority given to it under`
  line `that article;]`
  line
  line `(61) "sub-section" shall mean a sub-section of the section in which the word occurs;`
  line
  line `(62) "swear", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, shall include affirming`
  line `and declaring in the case of persons by law allowed to affirm or declare instead of swearing;`
  line
  line `^10[(62A) "Union territory" shall mean any Union territory specified in the First Schedule to the`
  line `Constitution and shall include any other territory comprised within the territory of India but not`
  line `specified in that Schedule;]`
  line
  line `(63) "vessel" shall include any ship or boat or any other description of vessel used in navigation;`
  line
  line `(64) "will" shall include a codicil and every writing making a voluntary posthumous disposition`
  line `of property;`
  line
  line `(65) expressions referring to "writing" shall be construed as including references to printing,`
  line `lithography, photography and other modes of representing or reproducing words in a visible form;`
  line and
  line
  line `(66) "year" shall mean a year reckoned according to the British calendar.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for section 3.`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 1) Order, 1956.`
  line
  line `3. Ins., ibid.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 1) Order, 1956.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 1) Order, 1956 for "a Part A State or a Part C State".`
  line
  line `6. Subs., ibid., for "under article 243 of the Constitution, and shall include".`
  line
  line `7. Subs., ibid., for clause (58).`
  line
  line `8. The word "and" omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 1) Order, 1956.`
  line
  line `9. Subs., ibid., for "or to be done after the commencement of the Constitution".`
  line
  line `10. Ins., ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (38533)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Application of foregoing definitions to previous enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38533&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The definitions in section 3 of`
  line `the following words and expressions, that is to say, "affidavit", "barrister",`
  line `^1*** "District Judge',`
  line `"father", ^2***, ^3***,`
  line `^4*** "immovable property", "imprisonment", ^5*** "Magistrate", "month", "movable`
  line `property", "oath", "person", "section", "son", "swear", "will", and "year" apply also, unless there is`
  line `anything repugnant in the subject or context, to all ^6[Central Acts] made after the third day of January,`
  line `1868, and to all Regulations made on or after the fourteenth day of January, 1887.`
  line
  line `(2) The definitions in the said section of the following words and expressions, that is to say, "abet",`
  line `"Chapter", "commencement", "financial year", "local authority", "master", "offence", 'part", "public`
  line `nuisance", "registered, schedule', "ship", "sign', "sub-section" and "writing" apply also, unless there is`
  line `anything repugnant in the subject or context, to all ^6[Central Acts] and Regulations made on or after the`
  line `fourteenth day of January, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "British India" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line `2. The words "Government of India" omitted, ibid.`
  line `3. The words "Her Majesty" or "the Queen" rep. by Act 18 of 1919, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line `4. The words "High Court" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line `5. The words "Local Government" omitted, ibid.`
  line `6. Subs., ibid., for "Acts of the Governor-General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (38534)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Application of certain definitions to Indian Laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for section 4A which was earlier inserted by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38534&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Application of certain definitions to Indian`
  line `Laws.--(1) The definitions in section 3 of the`
  line `expressions British India, Central Act, Central Government, Chief Controlling Revenue`
  line `Authority, Chief Revenue Authority, Constitution, Gazette, Government, Government`
  line `securities, High Court, India, Indian Law, Indian State, merged territories, Official Gazette,`
  line `Part A State, Part B State, Part C State, Provincial Government, State and State Government`
  line `shall apply, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context, to all Indian laws.`
  line
  line `(2) In any Indian law, references, by whatever form of words, to revenues of the Central Government`
  line `or of any State Government shall, on and from the first day of April, 1950, be construed as references to`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of India or the Consolidated Fund of the State, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (38535)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Coming into operation of enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38535&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Where any Central Act is not expressed to come`
  line `into operation on a particular day, then it shall come into operation on the day on which it receives the`
  line assent,--
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a Central Act made before the commencement of the Constitution, of the`
  line `Governor-General, and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an Act of Parliament, of the President.]`
  line
  line `^2**** *`
  line
  line `(3) Unless the contrary is expressed, a ^3[Central Act] or Regulation shall be construed as coming into`
  line `operation immediately on the expiration of the day preceding its commencement.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for sub-section (1).`
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted, ibid.`
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor-General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (38536)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 7
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38536&sectionno=5A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `[Coming into operation of Governor-General's Act.]`
  line `Rep. by the A.O. 1947. Earlier it was inserted by A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (38537)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Effect of repeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor-General in Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38537&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Where this Act, or any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, repeals any enactment hitherto made or hereafter to be made, then, unless a different intention appears, the repeal shall not--`
  line
  line `(a) revive anything not in force or existing at the time at which the repeal takes effect; or`
  line
  line `(b) affect the previous operation of any enactment so repealed or anything duly done or suffered`
  line `thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(c) affect any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under any`
  line `enactment so repealed; or`
  line
  line `(d) affect any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed`
  line `against any enactment so repealed; or`
  line
  line `(e) affect any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced, and any`
  line `such penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed as if the repealing Act or Regulation had not been`
  line passed.
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (38538)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 9
  title `Repeal of Act making textual amendment in Act or Regulation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38538&sectionno=6A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Repeal of Act making textual amendment in Act or`
  line `Regulation.--Where any ^2[Central Act] or Regulation made after the commencement of this Act repeals any enactment by which the text of any^2[Central Act] or Regulation was amended by the express omission, insertion or substitution of any matter, then, unless a different intention appears, the repeal shall not affect the continuance of any such amendment made by the enactment so repealed and in operation at the time of such repeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 1936, s. 2.`
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor-General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (38539)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 10
  title `Revival of repealed enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38539&sectionno=7&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, it shall be necessary, for the purpose of reviving, either wholly or partially,`
  line `any enactment wholly or partially repealed, expressly to state that purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies also to all ^2[Central Acts] made after the third day of January, 1868, and to all`
  line `Regulations made on or after the fourteenth day of January, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Acts of the Governor-General in Council".`
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "Acts of the Governor-General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (38540)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 11
  title `Construction of references to repealed enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38540&sectionno=8&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Where this Act, or any ^2[Central Act] or Regulation made after the commencement of this Act, repeals and re-enacts, with or without`
  line `modification, any provision of a former enactment, then references in any other enactment or in any`
  line `instrument to the provision so repealed shall, unless a different intention appears, be construed as`
  line `references to the provision so re-enacted.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) ^4[Where before the fifteenth day of August, 1947, any Act of Parliament of the United Kingdom`
  line `repealed and re-enacted], with or without modification, any provision of a former enactment, then`
  line `reference in any ^2[Central Act] or in any Regulation or instrument to the provision so repealed shall,`
  line `unless a different intention appears, be construed as references to the provision so re-enacted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 8 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 18 of 1919, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for Acts of the Governor-General in Council.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Where any Act of Parliament repeals and re-enacts".`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (38541)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 12
  title `Commencement and termination of time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38541&sectionno=9&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after`
  line `the commencement of this Act, it shall be sufficient, for the purpose of excluding the first in a series of`
  line `days or any other period of time, to use the word "from", and, for the purpose of including the last in a`
  line `series of days or any other period of time, to use the word "to".`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies also to all ^2[Central Acts] made after the third day of January, 1868, and to all Regulations made on or after the fourteenth day of January, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Acts of the Governor-General in Council".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "Acts of the Governor-General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (38542)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 13
  title `Computation of time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38542&sectionno=10&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, by any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, any act or proceeding is directed or allowed to be done or taken in any Court`
  line `or office on a certain day or within a prescribed period, then, if the Court or office is closed on that day or`
  line `the last day of the prescribed period, the act or proceeding shall be considered as done or taken in due`
  line `time if it is done or taken on the next day afterwards on which the Court or office is open:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to any act or proceeding to which the ^2Indian`
  line `Limitation Act, 1877 (15 of 1877), applies.`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies also to all ^3[Central Acts] and Regulations made on or after the fourteenth day`
  line `of January, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Acts of the Governor-General in Council".`
  line
  line `2. See now the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "Acts of the Governor-General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (38543)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 14
  title `Measurement of distances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Acts of the Governor-General in Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38543&sectionno=11&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `In the measurement of any distance, for the purposes of any`
  line `^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after the commencement of this Act, that distance shall, unless a`
  line `different intention appears, be measured in a straight line on a horizontal plane.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (38544)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 15
  title `Duty to be taken pro rata in enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38544&sectionno=12&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where, by any enactment now in force or hereafter`
  line `to be in force, any duty of customs or excise, or in the nature thereof, is leviable on any given quantity, by`
  line `weight, measure or value of any goods or merchandise, then a like duty is leviable according to the same`
  line `rate on any greater or less quantity.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (38545)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Gender and number.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs., ibid., for "Acts of the Governor-General in Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38545&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `In all ^1[Central Acts] and Regulations, unless there is anything repugnant`
  line `in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(1) words importing the masculine gender shall be taken to include females; and`
  line
  line `(2) words in the singular shall include the plural, and vice versa.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (38546)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 17
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38546&sectionno=13A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^113A. [References to the Sovereign.] Rep. by the`
  line `A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (38547)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers conferred to be exercisable from time to time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38547&sectionno=14&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, by any ^1[Central Act] or`
  line `Regulation made after the commencement of this Act, any power is conferred ^2***, then ^3[unless a different intention appears] that power may be exercised from time to time as occasion requires.`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies also to all ^4[Central Acts] and Regulations made on or after the fourteenth day of January, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  line
  line `2. The words "on the Government" omitted by Act 18 of 1919, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 1919, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Acts of the Governor General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (38548)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to appoint to include power to appoint ex officio.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council"`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38548&sectionno=15&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Where, by any ^1[Central Act] or`
  line `Regulation, a power to appoint any person to fill any office or execute any function is conferred, then,`
  line `unless it is otherwise expressly provided, any such appointment, if it is made after the commencement of`
  line `this Act, may be made either by name or by virtue of office.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (38549)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to appoint to include power to suspend or dismiss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38549&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Where, by any ^1[Central Act] or`
  line `Regulation, a power to make any appointment is conferred, then, unless a different intention appears, the`
  line `authority having ^2[for the time being] power to make the appointment shall also have power to suspend or`
  line `dismiss any person appointed ^3[whether by itself or any other authority] in exercise of that power.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 1928, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 1928, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for "by it".`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (38550)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Substitution of functionaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38550&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, it shall be sufficient, for the purpose of indicating the application of a law to`
  line `every person or number of persons for the time being executing the functions of an office, to mention the`
  line `official title of the officer at present executing the functions, or that of the officer by whom the functions`
  line `are commonly executed.`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies also to all ^2[Central Acts] made after the third day of January, 1868, and to all`
  line `Regulations made on or after the fourteenth day of January, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Acts of the Governor General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (38551)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title Successors.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38551&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after the commencement of this Act, it`
  line `shall be sufficient, for the purpose of indicating the relation of a law to the successors of any functionaries`
  line `or of corporations having perpetual succession, to express its relation to the functionaries or corporations.`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies also to all ^2[Central Acts] made after the third day of January, 1868, and to all Regulations made on or after the fourteenth day of January, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council"`
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Acts of the Governor General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (38552)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Official chiefs and subordinates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38552&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, it shall be sufficient, for the purpose of expressing that a law relative to the`
  line `chief or superior of an office shall apply to the deputies or subordinates lawfully performing the duties of`
  line `that office in the place of their superior, to prescribe the duty of the superior.`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies also to all ^2[Central Acts] made after the third day of January, 1868, and to all`
  line `Regulations made on or after the fourteenth day of January, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Acts of the Governor General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (38553)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Construction of orders, etc., issued under enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38553&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where, by any ^1[Central Act] or`
  line `Regulation, a power to issue any ^2[notification], order, scheme, rule, form, or bye-law is conferred, then`
  line `expressions used in the ^2[notification], order, scheme, rule, form or bye-law, if it is made after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, shall, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context, have the`
  line `same respective meanings as in the Act or Regulation conferring the power.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council"`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 1903, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (38565)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to issue, to include power to add to, amend, vary or rescind notifications, orders, rules or bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38565&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where, by any ^1[Central Act] or Regulations a power to ^2`
  line `[issue notifications,]`
  line `orders, rules or bye-laws is conferred, then that power includes a power, exercisable in the like manner`
  line `and subject to the like sanction and conditions (if any), to add to, amend, vary or rescind any`
  line `^3[notifications,] orders, rules or bye-laws so ^4[issued].`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 1903, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "make".`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid.`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid., for "made".`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (38566)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title `Making of rules or bye-laws and issuing of orders between passing and commencement of enactment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38566&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where, by any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation which is not to come into force immediately,`
  line `on the passing thereof, a power is conferred to make rules or bye-laws, or to issue orders with respect to`
  line `the application of the Act or Regulation, or with respect to the establishment of any Court or office or the`
  line `appointment of any Judge or officer thereunder, of with respect to the person by whom, or the time when,`
  line `or the place where, or the manner in which, or the fees for which, anything is to be done under the Act or`
  line `Regulation, then that power may be exercised at any time after the passing of the Act or Regulation; but`
  line `rules, bye-laws or orders so made or issued shall not take effect till the commencement of the Act or`
  line Regulation.
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (38556)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 27
  title `Provisions applicable to making of rules or bye-laws after previous publication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38556&sectionno=23&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where, by`
  line `any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation, a power to make rules or bye-laws is expressed to be given subject to`
  line `the condition of the rules or bye-laws being made after previous publication, then the following`
  line `provisions shall apply, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) the authority having power to make the rules or bye-laws shall, before making them, publish a`
  line `draft of the proposed rules or bye-laws for the information of persons likely to be affected thereby;`
  line
  line `(2) the publication shall be made in such manner as that authority deems to be sufficient, or, if the`
  line `condition with respect to previous publication so requires, in such manner as the ^2[Government concerned] prescribes;`
  line
  line `(3) there shall be published with the draft a notice specifying a date on or after which the draft`
  line `will be taken into consideration;`
  line
  line `(4) the authority having power to make the rules or bye-laws, and, where the rules or bye-laws are`
  line `to be made with the sanction, approval or concurrence of another authority, that authority also, shall`
  line `consider any objection or suggestion which may be received by the authority having power to make`
  line `the rules or bye-laws from any person with respect to the draft before the date so specified;`
  line
  line `(5) the publication in the ^3[Official Gazette] of a rule or bye-law purporting to have been made in`
  line `exercise of a power to make rules or bye-laws after previous publication shall be conclusive proof`
  line `that the rule or bye-law has been duly made.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Central Government or the Provincial Government".`
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (38557)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 28
  title `Continuation of orders, etc., issued under enactments repealed and re-enacted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38557&sectionno=24&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line Where
  line `any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation, is, after the commencement of this Act, repealed and re-enacted with or`
  line `without modification, then, unless it is otherwise expressly provided any ^2[appointment notification],`
  line `order, scheme, rule, form or bye-law, ^2[made or] issued under the repealed Act or Regulation, shall, so far`
  line `as it is not inconsistent with the provisions re-enacted, continue in force, and be deemed to have`
  line `been ^2[made or] issued under the provisions so re-enacted, unless and until it is superseded by`
  line `any ^2[appointment notification,] order, scheme, rule, form or bye-law, ^2[made or] issued under the`
  line `provisions so re-enacted ^3[and when any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation, which, by a notification under`
  line `section 5 or 5A of the ^4Scheduled Districts Act, 1874, (14 of 1874) or any like law, has been extended to`
  line `any local area, has, by a subsequent notification, been withdrawn from the re-extended to such area or any`
  line `part thereof, the provisions of such Act or Regulation shall be deemed to have been repealed and`
  line `re-enacted in such area or part within the meaning of this section].`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  line `2. Ins. by the A.O. 1937, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 1914, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line `4. Rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (38558)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 29
  title `Recovery of fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. See, the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38558&sectionno=25&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Sections 63 to 70 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the provisions`
  line `of the ^1Code of Criminal Procedure for the time being in force in relation to the issue and the execution of`
  line `warrants for the levy of fines shall apply to all fines imposed under any Act, Regulation, rule or bye-law,`
  line `unless the Act, Regulation, rule or bye-law contains an express provision to the contrary.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (38559)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 30
  title `Provision as to offences punishable under two or more enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38559&sectionno=26&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where an act or`
  line `omission constitutes an offence under two or more enactments, then the offender shall be liable to be`
  line `prosecuted and punished under either or any of those enactments, but shall not be liable to be punished`
  line `twice for the same offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (38560)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 31
  title `Meaning of service by post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38560&sectionno=27&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Where any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after the`
  line `commencement of this Act authorizes or requires any document to be served by post, whether the`
  line `expression "serve" or either of the expressions "give" or send or any other expression is used, then,`
  line `unless a different intention appears, the service shall be deemed to be effected by properly addressing,`
  line `pre-paying and posting by registered post, a letter containing the document, and, unless the contrary is`
  line `proved, to have been effected at the time at which the letter would be delivered in the ordinary course of`
  line post.
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (38561)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 32
  title `Citation of enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for" Act of the Governor General in Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38561&sectionno=28&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation, and in any rule, bye-law,`
  line `instrument or document, made under, or with reference to any such Act or Regulation, any enactment`
  line `may be cited by reference to the title or short title (if any) conferred thereon or by reference to the number`
  line `and year thereof, and any provision in an enactment may be cited by reference to the section or subsection of the enactment in which the provision is contained.`
  line
  line `(2) In this Act and in any ^1[Central Act] or Regulation made after the commencement of this Act, a`
  line `description or citation of a portion of another enactment shall, unless a different intention appears, be`
  line `construed as including the word, section or other part mentioned or referred to as forming the beginning`
  line `and as forming the end of the portion comprised in the description or citation.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (38562)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 33
  title `Saving for previous enactments, rules and bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38562&sectionno=29&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act respecting the`
  line `construction of Acts, Regulations, rules or bye-laws made after the commencement of this Act shall not`
  line `affect the construction of any Act, Regulation, rule or bye-law made before the commencement of this`
  line `Act, although the Act, Regulation, rule or bye-law is continued or amended by an Act, Regulation, rule or`
  line `bye-law made after the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (38563)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 34
  title `Application of Act to Ordinances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854&sectionId=38563&sectionno=30&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00050_189710_1523337761854
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30.Application of Act to Ordinances.--In this Act the`
  line `expression ^2[Central Act], wherever it`
  line `occurs, except in section 5 and the word "Act" in ^3[clauses (9), (13), (25), (40), (43), (52) and (54)] of`
  line `section 3 and in section 25 shall be deemed to include an Ordinance made and promulgated by the`
  line `Governor General under section 23 of the Indian Councils Act, 1861 ^4`
  line `[or section 72 of the Government of`
  line `India Act, 1915,] ^5`
  line `[or section 42 ^6`
  line `*** of the Government of India Act, 1935] ^7`
  line `[and an Ordinance`
  line `promulgated by the President under article 123 of the Constitution].]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 1914, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Act of the Governor General in Counci"l.`
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, "for clauses (9), (12), (38), (48) and (50)".`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 24 of 1917, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line `5. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line `6. The words and figures "or section" 43 omitted by the A.O. 1947.`
  line `7. Added by the A.O. 1950.`
